.TH "snd_soc_jack_report" 9 "snd_soc_jack_report" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_jack_report \- Report the current status for a jack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_soc_jack_report
.BI "(struct snd_soc_jack *jack "  ","
.BI "int status "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "jack" 12
the jack
.IP "status" 12
a bitmask of enum snd_jack_type values that are currently detected.
.IP "mask" 12
a bitmask of enum snd_jack_type values that being reported.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If configured using \fBsnd_soc_jack_add_pins\fP then the associated
DAPM pins will be enabled or disabled as appropriate and DAPM
synchronised.
.SH "NOTE"
This function uses mutexes and should be called from a
context which can sleep (such as a workqueue).
